I mean,
you're college-educated.

14:47.420 --> 14:49.222
Honey, no no no, no.
No, no.

14:49.256 --> 14:52.325
Do-- Don't, don't,
don't, don't, don't open...

14:52.359 --> 14:54.394
Finally!
I ordered Chinese.

14:54.427 --> 14:57.064
You don't happen to have any
bottled water with you, do you?

14:57.097 --> 14:58.398
I'm sorry, what?

14:58.431 --> 14:59.967
Oh, honey,
you have your night guard in,

15:00.000 --> 15:01.234
so it's kind of hard
to understand --

15:01.268 --> 15:03.136
[ Night guard clacks ]

15:03.170 --> 15:06.273
[ Normal voice ] Bottled water.
Do you have any bottled water?

15:06.306 --> 15:07.574
Not unless you ordered it.

15:07.607 --> 15:09.977
[ Sighs ]

15:10.010 --> 15:11.344
What are you doing?

15:11.378 --> 15:12.712
I'm going to walk forwards
until I find a store

15:12.745 --> 15:14.281
that sells bottled water!

15:14.314 --> 15:17.584
Breathing tap water.
What is this, Haiti?

15:17.617 --> 15:20.087
I'll get your money.

15:23.190 --> 15:25.625
[ Lighter clicks ]

15:25.658 --> 15:27.594
[ Flame crackles ]

15:31.198 --> 15:32.432
[ Exhales ]

15:32.465 --> 15:33.633
[ Crash ]

15:33.666 --> 15:35.202
[ Sandy yells ]

15:35.235 --> 15:39.139
[ Animals howling and hooting ]

15:39.172 --> 15:40.607
[ Bicycle bell rings ]

15:40.640 --> 15:42.575
So here I am,

15:42.609 --> 15:44.611
getting ready to execute
my latest plan.

15:44.644 --> 15:47.080
If I could just buy myself
a few hours,

15:47.114 --> 15:49.582
I could convince Sandy I was
sober enough to drive home.

15:49.616 --> 15:51.118
But the guy would be back
with the tape soon,

15:51.151 --> 15:52.485
and this time,
he would be ready

15:52.519 --> 15:54.187
for me to try
and smash it again,

15:54.221 --> 15:56.223
so I searched all over
your cabin for a weapon.

15:56.256 --> 15:59.159
**

16:13.506 --> 16:15.508
The only way I was
going to overpower this guy

16:15.542 --> 16:17.444
was to use
the element of surprise.

16:17.477 --> 16:20.313
So, taking a page
out of Sir Isaac Newton's book,

16:20.347 --> 16:21.581
I made my own cradle.

16:28.755 --> 16:32.025
When this ball hits his balls,
he'll drop the tape.

16:32.059 --> 16:34.461
Then I'll scurry down
and smash it again.

16:34.494 --> 16:37.464
That should buy me
some more time.

16:37.497 --> 16:40.133
Anyway, I'm writing all this
down in your guest book

16:40.167 --> 16:42.135
so you can give it to
the police in case he kills me.

16:42.169 --> 16:45.738
[ Footsteps approaching ]

16:45.772 --> 16:47.540
Hello?

16:47.574 --> 16:49.609
**

17:02.789 --> 17:05.092
Oh, shit.

17:09.662 --> 17:15.802
[ Bird calling in distance ]

17:15.835 --> 17:18.438
[ Whispers ] Hey.

17:25.378 --> 17:26.613
[ Snaps fingers ]

17:30.650 --> 17:32.152
[ Lips flapping ]

17:32.185 --> 17:34.421
Okay.

17:34.454 --> 17:35.855
[ Bird continues calling ]

17:35.888 --> 17:37.290
[ Heartbeat ]

17:37.324 --> 17:39.792
[ Sighs ]

17:39.826 --> 17:42.329
**

17:52.739 --> 17:58.145
Oh, boy. Okay. All right.

17:58.178 --> 18:01.114
[ Slurring ] Timmy!
There's my Timmy!

18:01.148 --> 18:04.651
Oh, my God, the guy at the store
was totally hitting on me!

18:04.684 --> 18:06.553
He said
my tits were leaking,

18:06.586 --> 18:08.221
but how would he know
my tits were leaking

18:08.255 --> 18:10.690
if he wasn't looking
right at 'em, right?

18:10.723 --> 18:12.425
[ Laughs nervously ]
I am on fire!

18:12.459 --> 18:13.526
[ Laughs ]
Mm.

18:13.560 --> 18:15.295
All right. Whoa!

18:15.328 --> 18:17.397
[ Glass shatters ]
Mmm! [ Smooching ]

18:17.430 --> 18:21.401
So, in the end,
things turned out okay.

18:21.434 --> 18:24.871
I was able to put
your bowling-ball lamp
back the way it was.

18:24.904 --> 18:27.140
The owl was a little trickier.

18:27.174 --> 18:31.378
This turned out to be
exactly the weekend
my wife and I needed.

18:33.513 --> 18:35.782
Thanks for sharing
your home with us.

18:35.815 --> 18:38.185
Your pal, John.
[ Seatbelt clicks ]

18:40.587 --> 18:41.921
P.S., that's not my real name.
[ Engine starts ]

18:41.954 --> 18:44.191
[ "I Need Never Get Old" plays ]

18:52.599 --> 18:54.801
[ Car alarm chirps ]

18:54.834 --> 18:57.337
Frank: Shit!
[ Pounding on trunk ]

18:57.370 --> 19:00.507
**

19:09.982 --> 19:12.452
* Can we be there

19:12.485 --> 19:14.621
* Oh, just think of the time

19:16.623 --> 19:19.292
* Thought of love so strange

19:19.326 --> 19:21.494
* Said you never knew

19:23.863 --> 19:26.866
* While I try my best

19:26.899 --> 19:28.835
* To cover our eyes

19:30.937 --> 19:35.174
* It's a common way to blame
and hide the truth *

19:37.744 --> 19:40.847
* I know that some will say

19:40.880 --> 19:44.317
* It matters but little, babe

19:44.351 --> 19:47.420
* Aw, but come on
and mean it to me *

19:47.454 --> 19:49.622
* I need it so bad

19:49.656 --> 19:51.591
[ Computer chimes ]

19:53.560 --> 19:56.896
* I needed to try

19:56.929 --> 20:00.600
* I needed it so

20:00.633 --> 20:03.336
* I needed your love,
I'm burning away *

20:03.370 --> 20:06.339
[ Door closes ]
* I need never get old

20:06.373 --> 20:07.807
Hello.

20:07.840 --> 20:09.442
Oh, hi.

20:09.476 --> 20:11.811
We're here to pick up the keys
for Froggy Cottage.

20:11.844 --> 20:14.347
Oh. Of course.
[ Keyboard clacks ]

20:14.381 --> 20:18.385
Let me, uh -- let me find
your reservations.

20:18.418 --> 20:20.587
[ Birds chirping ]

20:21.788 --> 20:23.523
Jeff: Are you sure you want
to go through with this?

20:23.556 --> 20:25.425
We could go to jail,
you know.

20:25.458 --> 20:27.460
Don't get soft
on me now, Jeff.

20:27.494 --> 20:29.329
We've got some heavy lifting
for the Lord to do.

20:29.362 --> 20:31.664
Our son is not marrying
an atheist.

20:31.698 --> 20:34.301
Okeydoke.

20:34.334 --> 20:36.303
[ Ominous music playing ]
